	<h1><a href="showthread.php?74130-XBMC-amp-TV-Shows">XBMC &amp; TV Shows</a></h1>
	<p class="description">Printable View</p>
</div>



<ul id="postlist">
	<li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_1">
	<div class="header">
		<div class="datetime">September 15th, 2012, 05:06 AM</div>
		<span class="username">Yaxa</span>
	</div>
	
	
		<div class="title">XBMC &amp; TV Shows</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">I'm having major problems getting XBMC to recognize my TV shows, and I really don't want to change the way I sort/store them. I'm hoping maybe someone here ran into the same problem and found a solution.<br />
<br />
My TV shows are stored as such:<br />
<br />
X:\MP4\TV\<b>[TV Show Name]</b> Season <b>[Season Number]</b>\<b>[Episode Number]</b> Episode Title.m4v<br />
<br />
e.g.<br />
<br />
X:\MP4\TV\Battlestar Galactica Season 1\01 33.m4v<br />
X:\MP4\TV\Battlestar Galactica Season 1\02 Water.m4v<br />
etc.<br />
<br />
I set up an advancedsettings.xml with the follow regex for my case of <b>[Season Number]</b>\<b>[Episode Number]</b>, as suggested by the XBMC wiki:<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_description">Code:</div>
	<hr /><code class="bbcode_code">&lt;advancedsettings&gt;<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;tvshowmatching&gt;<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;regexp&gt;Season[\._ ]([0-9]+)[\\/]([0-9]+)[^\\/]*&lt;/regexp&gt;<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;/tvshowmatching&gt;<br />
&lt;/advancedsettings&gt;</code><hr />
</div>However, that doesn't seem to help at all. It only finds some single-season TV shows, but not even any episodes for those.<br />
<br />
The files are already fully tagged for iTunes (names, numbers, description, rating, etc), but apparently XBMC still can't read MP4 video tags.<br />
<br />
Any suggestions other than simply sticking with iTunes for TV shows?</blockquote>
	</div>
</li><li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_2">
	<div class="header">
		<div class="datetime">September 16th, 2012, 02:27 PM</div>
		<span class="username">Delaregar</span>
	</div>
	
	
		<div class="title">Re: XBMC &amp; TV Shows</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">That regular expression only matches strings starting with &quot;Season&quot;. I'd try adding .* at the front to match the text that comes before &quot;Season&quot;.<br />
<br />
&quot;.*&quot; means 0 or more of any character.</blockquote>
	</div>
</li><li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_3">
	<div class="header">
